


installation:

  To install an archiver instance involves generating a configuration xml 
and intializing the database accordingly.

Step 1: Database intialization

  The automated script, ta_initdb.sh, can be used to automatically generate
the database specifics by first modifying ta_dbcredentials.conf with the 
following options:

TCANMS_DBUSER=
TCANMS_DBPASS=
TCANMS_DBHOST=

 The script will generate the necessary SQL and create the database and exec
 the SQL via the config script 'tcanms_dbinit.sh'. 
 
 This script will assume all SQL is exec'd by the root sql account. If your 
 database 'root' user is not named 'root' or you wish to use a different 
 account, then you must run the tcanms_dbinit.sh script by hand. 
 
  1. First run 'ta_createdbsql.sh' with the name of the database 
     and the name of the sql file to generate.
  2. Run the 'tcanms_dbinit.sh' script using the -D and -f options providing 
     the database name and sql file generated in step 1, respectively, and 
     providing the db account details with proper permissions for creating 
     the database.
     (see 'tcanms_dbinit.sh --help' for more details)

